==English==

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|/ˈbæ.ɹə.ni/|lang=en}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|baronies}}

# The [[domain]] of a [[baron]] or [[baroness]], [[usually]] as [[part]] of a [[larger]] [[kingdom]] or [[empire]].
## {{lb|en|historical|Ireland}} {{synonym of|hundred|nodot=1|lang=en}}, an [[English]] [[administrative]] [[division]] [[originally]] [[reckoned]] as [[comprising]] 100 [[hide]]s and in [[various]] [[number]]s [[composing]] [[counties]].
##* {{ante|1687}} W. Petty, ''The Political Anatomy of Ireland'', page 326:
##*: In Ireland... an<!--sic--> head constable for each '''barony''' or hundred, being 252.
##* '''1873''', General Report on the Census of England, volume IV, page 181:
##*: The '''Baronies''' appear to have been formed successively on the submission of the Irish chiefs... the territory of each constituting a '''barony'''.
## {{lb|en|Scotland}} Any [[large]] [[manor]] or [[estate]], [[regardless]] of its [[owner]]'s [[rank]].
# {{lb|en|obsolete}} The [[baronage]]: the [[body]] of [[barons]] in a [[realm]].
# [[baronship|Baronship]], the [[rank]] or [[position]] of a [[baron]].
# {{lb|en|law}} The [[legal]] [[tenure]] of a [[baron]]'s [[land]]; [[military]] [[tenure]].

